criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  American Society of Anesthesiology (ASA) physical fitness classification grade I-III

          -  patients who underwent elective total knee arthroplasty surgery

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with a past history of sleep apnea syndrome and/or other sleep disorders;

          -  Patients requiring the long-term use of hypnotics and sedatives;

          -  Patients with a past history of mental disorders and psychological disorders and the
             recent use of antipsychotic drugs and anti-depression drugs;

          -  Patients who were unable to undergo or refused sleep studies i.e. polysomnography
             (PSM).
